    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_a80b6b22",
      "file_path": "build/download_offline_data_by_lists.sh",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 85,
      "message": "As this is application related (onap) not offline installer related. Just wondering should we separate such stuff sohow out from installer visible it's app specific?\nIn new packaging also there was already some separation of \"additional\" stuff.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3957,
        "name": "Samuli Silvius",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
        "username": "silvius"
      },
      "updated": "2019-01-31 11:41:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5434aa4c_a4c22a1d",
      "file_path": "build/download_offline_data_by_lists.sh",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 85,
      "message": "Whole are building / packaging is currently tailored for casablanca and all people using this installer are using it for casablanca now. Please keep this in mind. Of course we should try to be generic, but for instance this \"auxilionary/additional\" stuff in packaging can be currently used just for inserting docker images in runtime into nexus. As per latest research made by Milan we don't think it's suitable to use nexus for rpm/deb storing (i dont recall details why now) so this stuff must be covered outside of nexus for now anyway it's another discussion not related to downloading. I would prefer to download everything from one place like this one. Maybe we should better document it or make it as optional part but I would wait for it once such requirement will really materialise",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4009,
        "name": "Michal Ptacek",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "m.ptacek@partner.samsung.com",
        "username": "Michal.Ptacek"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-01 10:00:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9adffdf1_a80b6b22",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "c0b15f70_e1676b27",
      "file_path": "build/download_offline_data_by_lists.sh",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 85,
      "message": "Actually for the rpms we are able to put them to nexus without any problem (we just need to keep some out, because they are needed before the nexus is run). For the deb packages - we would need to rebuild the nexus container to add the deb repository plugin in, because currently the plugin is not in the official nexus.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5000,
        "name": "Tom�? Levora",
        "display_name": "Tomáš Levora",
        "email": "tomas.levora@gmail.com",
        "username": "Tomas.Levora"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-01 10:27:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5434aa4c_a4c22a1d",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "b5dc9719_bb28dfc0",
      "file_path": "build/download_offline_data_by_lists.sh",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 85,
      "message": "ok, so it might be worth for keep tracking for the future. Nevertheless this is about downloading and my point is that we should download everything we need on single place. it's definitely inside packaging for our platform now.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4009,
        "name": "Michal Ptacek",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "m.ptacek@partner.samsung.com",
        "username": "Michal.Ptacek"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-01 10:37:42.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c0b15f70_e1676b27",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "8a25ccdd_f43d02a1",
      "file_path": "build/download_offline_data_by_lists.sh",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 85,
      "message": "Yes it should be tracked. And introducing \"additional\" packages into downloading and moving these ONAP related packages out from here into own script, does not break your further steps with nexus or anything. Then we just have this part as clearly separated downloded content.\nThis script can run it and still place the content to very same place.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3957,
        "name": "Samuli Silvius",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
        "username": "silvius"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-01 11:13:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "b5dc9719_bb28dfc0",
      "unresolved": false
